soln_description:
To prove: Let $x_{0}=\frac{1}{n}, 0 \leq x \leq 1, \beta=\sqrt{1+2 x_{0}}, f(x)=\sqrt{n x}, g(x)=\frac{\sqrt{n}+\sqrt{n+2}}{\sqrt{n}+\sqrt{n+2 n x}}=\frac{1+\beta}{1+\sqrt{1+2 x}}$, then the original inequality is equivalent to proving $\left(\frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} f\left(x_{i}\right)\right)\left(\frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} g\left(x_{i}\right)\right) \leq 1$;

Since $f(x)=1+f^{\prime}\left(x_{0}\right)\left(x-x_{0}\right)-\frac{H(x)}{2}, g(x)=1+g^{\prime}\left(x_{0}\right)\left(x-x_{0}\right)-\frac{G(x)}{2}$,

where $f^{\prime}\left(x_{0}\right)=\frac{n}{2}, H(x)=(\sqrt{n x}-1)^{2}, G(x)=\frac{(\sqrt{1+2 x}-\beta)^{2}}{1+\beta}\left(\frac{2}{1+\sqrt{1+2 x}}+\frac{1}{\beta}\right)$, and $G(x) \leq(\sqrt{1+2 x}-\beta)^{2} \leq(\sqrt{1+2 x}-\beta)^{2}\left(\frac{\sqrt{1+2 x}+\sqrt{1+2 x_{0}}}{\sqrt{2 x}+\sqrt{2 x_{0}}}\right)=\frac{2}{n}(\sqrt{n x}-1)^{2} \leq H(x)$.

Also, $\sum_{i=1}^{n}\left(x_{i}-x_{0}\right)=0$, hence
$$
\begin{aligned}
\left(\frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} f\left(x_{i}\right)\right)\left(\frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} g\left(x_{i}\right)\right) & =\left(1-\frac{1}{2 n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} H\left(x_{i}\right)\right)\left(1-\frac{1}{2 n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} G\left(x_{i}\right)\right) \\
& \leq\left(1-\frac{1}{2 n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} H\left(x_{i}\right)\right)\left(1+\frac{1}{2 n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} H\left(x_{i}\right)\right) \leq 1
\end{aligned}
$$

